<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8911] Admin UI: solr-impl and lucene-impl versions are cut off in SNAPSHOT versions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8911</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I just tried to see Solr&apos;s &quot;compiled on&quot; date on my dev Solr server, which is running a 5.5.1-SNAPSHOT version, compiled from the branch_5_5 source.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &quot;impl&quot; strings are so long that the only thing I could tell is that it was compiled this year.  I will attach a screenshot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It wasn&apos;t possible to see or highlight the full string.  I did manage to see it all when I maximized my browser window (on a 1680x1050 screen), but I really dislike running with windows maximized.  It&apos;s not like I keep the windows &lt;b&gt;small&lt;/b&gt; either &amp;#8211; the screenshot will reflect this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12953993">SOLR-8911</key>
